SIMPLE: waffle
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Waffle
<hw>Waffle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>wafel</ets>.
See <er>Wafer</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A thin cake baked and then
rolled; a wafer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A soft indented cake cooked in a waffle
iron.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Waffle iron</b></col>, <cd>an iron utensil or mold made
in two parts shutting together, -- used for cooking waffles over a
fire.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Waft</ent>⟦br⟧
